    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-03-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-03-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="38"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d38">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.20/3–1148</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        British Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Inverchapel</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-03-12">March 12,
                            1948</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Ambassador</hi>: Please inform Mr. Bevin that in
                    accordance Avith your <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> of March 11, 1948, Ave
                    are prepared to proceed at once in the joint discussions on the establishment of
                    an Atlantic security system.</p>
                <p>I suggest the prompt arrival of the British representative early next week.</p>
                <p>Faithfully yours,</p>
                <p rend="right">[File copy not signed]</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
